
Antibody Epitope Prediction tool
================================

Introduction:
-------------
The distributions 'IEDB_BCell-1.0.tar.gz' contain a collection methods for Antibody Epitope Prediction.
The collection is a mixture of python scripts, specific binary for BepiPred and a pickled file containing residue scales for different methods.

Prerequisites:
--------------
+ Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 64-bit environment
  * http://www.redhat.com/
    - This distribution has been tested on Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 64 bit system.

+ Python 2.5 or higher
  * http://www.python.org/
    - Under ubuntu: sudo apt-get install python2.5
    
+ Matplotlib
  * http://matplotlib.org/
    - Under ubuntu: sudo apt-get install python-matplotlib
    
+ gawk 
  * http://www.gnu.org/software/gawk/manual/gawk.html#Installation
    - Under ubuntu: sudo apt-get install gawk

Installation:
-------------
Unpack the tar.gz files (IEDB_BCell-1.0.tar.gz)

  $ tar -zxvf IEDB_BCell-1.0.tar.gz
  $ cd bcell
  $ ./configure.py
  
Available prediction methods are:
---------------------------------
Chou-Fasman
Emini
Karplus-Schulz
Kolaskar-Tongaonkar
Parker
Bepipred

Available commands: 
-------------------
python predict_bcell.py -m [method-name] [input-file]
python predict_bcell.py -m [method-name] --swissprot [swissprot-id]

Example:
--------
python predict_bcell.py -m Chou-Fasman example/test.txt
python predict_bcell.py -m Chou-Fasman --swissprot P02185

